Argentine Stocks: Galicia, Petrobras and Tenaris Decline

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-02-24T20:25:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/argentine-stocks-molinos-and-tenaris-fall-petrobras-rises.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 3:01 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 1.4 percent to 3,382.71, its sixth
straight day of losses.    Grupo Financiero Galicia SA  (GGAL AF) retreated 2.2 percent
to 5.91 pesos, its lowest price in 10 weeks and its fourth
consecutive day of losses. Argentina’s largest consumer lender
fell as the price of sovereign bonds in Argentina declined,
which signals lower value for banks’ fixed-income holdings.    Tenaris SA  (TS AF) lost 4.7 percent to 93.6 pesos, its
steepest plunge in six weeks. The world’s largest producer of
seamless steel tubes used in the oil industry had its
recommendation cut to “hold” from “buy” at Bank of America
Corp.    Petroleo Brasileiro SA  (APBR AF) fell 0.7 percent to 80.6
pesos. Brazil’s state-controlled oil company fell in line with
crude prices, which snapped a five-day rising streak on
assurances from the U.S. and  Saudi Arabia  that they can
compensate for any disruptions of Libyan shipments.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
